docs.abstract: The billionaire philanthropist, appearing in Iowa as he mulls a presidential run, called climate change “the issue’’ for 2020.
docs.snippet: The billionaire philanthropist, appearing in Iowa as he mulls a presidential run, called climate change “the issue’’ for 2020.
docs.lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa — On a wintry day, Michael R. Bloomberg stood in black tassel loafers in melting snow while he inspected solar panels on a rooftop, then said he would make climate change “the issue” of the 2020 presidential race.

headline.main: Bloomberg, Focusing on Climate Change, Says He Would Battle the Coal Industry
headline.print_headline: In Iowa, Bloomberg Says He’d Make Environment  ‘The Issue’ of 2020 Race

docs.abstract: Dozens of possible 2020 Democratic candidates are mulling, weighing, considering, wondering. Here is a guide to how they are communicating a desire to run without announcing it outright.

docs.abstract: The former Virginia governor concluded that his moderate profile would have limited appeal when Democrats appear to be choosing between younger, progressive contenders and veteran politicians.
docs.snippet: The former Virginia governor concluded that his moderate profile would have limited appeal when Democrats appear to be choosing between younger, progressive contenders and veteran politicians.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Gov. Terry McAuliffe of Virginia said Wednesday he would not run for president, concluding that his moderate profile would have limited appeal when Democratic voters appear to be choosing between younger, progressive contenders and veteran politicians like Senator Bernie Sanders and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., who is expected to enter the race next week.

headline.main: Terry McAuliffe Will Not Run for President

docs.abstract: L. McCrae Dowless, the man at the center of the investigation of possible election fraud in North Carolina’s Ninth District, was investigated for similar conduct in the past.
docs.snippet: L. McCrae Dowless, the man at the center of the investigation of possible election fraud in North Carolina’s Ninth District, was investigated for similar conduct in the past.
docs.lead_paragraph: In early 2018, officials at North Carolina’s elections board were worried about the integrity of the coming midterm elections in rural Bladen County — particularly because of the possibility that a political operative named L. McCrae Dowless Jr. might run a worrisome absentee-ballot program similar to one they had seen him run there two years earlier.

headline.main: North Carolina Election Contractor Was Investigated for Possible Fraud in 2016 Race
headline.print_headline: Worker in Disputed North Carolina Race Had Been Investigated for Fraud Before

docs.abstract: Mr. Sanders’s income shot up after his last presidential bid, topping $1 million in 2016 and 2017 as proceeds from books drove up his earnings.
docs.snippet: Mr. Sanders’s income shot up after his last presidential bid, topping $1 million in 2016 and 2017 as proceeds from books drove up his earnings.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, a leading candidate for the Democratic presidential nomination, disclosed 10 years of tax returns on Monday, providing a more detailed look at his finances than what he offered when he ran for the White House in 2016.

headline.main: Bernie Sanders Released His Tax Returns. He’s Part of the 1%.
headline.print_headline: A ‘Fortunate’ Sanders Releases Tax Returns. He’s Now Part of the One Percent.

docs.abstract: Mr. McCain urged former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to “not walk away” from politics, and said he wished he had chosen Joseph I. Lieberman, not Sarah Palin, as his running mate in 2008.
docs.snippet: Mr. McCain urged former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to “not walk away” from politics, and said he wished he had chosen Joseph I. Lieberman, not Sarah Palin, as his running mate in 2008.
docs.lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — When former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. traveled to Senator John McCain’s Arizona ranch last Sunday to spend a few hours with his ailing friend, the two reminisced about the “crazy senators” they had served with, the overseas trips they took together for decades and the friendship Mr. McCain forged with Mr. Biden’s two sons.

headline.main: At His Ranch, John McCain Shares Memories and Regrets With Friends
headline.print_headline: At Home, McCain Shares Memories and Regrets

docs.abstract: The former state senator benefited from more than $1 million in outside spending by Republican groups determined to avoid repeats of losses in Alabama and Pennsylvania.
docs.snippet: The former state senator benefited from more than $1 million in outside spending by Republican groups determined to avoid repeats of losses in Alabama and Pennsylvania.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The former Arizona state senator Debbie Lesko fended off an unusually strong Democratic challenge to win a special congressional election on Tuesday, according to The Associated Press, demonstrating the resilience of the Republican base but also the eagerness of liberals to compete in even the most heavily conservative districts.

headline.main: Debbie Lesko Wins Arizona Special Election for Congress, Rallying G.O.P.
headline.print_headline: Republican Wins Race In Arizona Stronghold, Buoying Nervous Party

docs.abstract: Mr. Kelly, the former astronaut who is married to Gabrielle Giffords, is challenging Republican Senator Martha McSally, who was appointed to the seat that had been left vacant by John McCain’s death.
docs.snippet: Mr. Kelly, the former astronaut who is married to Gabrielle Giffords, is challenging Republican Senator Martha McSally, who was appointed to the seat that had been left vacant by John McCain’s death.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mark Kelly, the former astronaut and gun-control activist who is married to Gabrielle Giffords, announced on Tuesday that he would run for Senate in Arizona, challenging appointed Senator Martha McSally and intensifying the Democratic threat to Republicans’ narrow control of the chamber.

headline.main: Mark Kelly to Run for Senate in Arizona
